<paragraph base="SL29738" id="IAS07_11"><paranum>11</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 7"/><data name="paranum" value="11"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS07_P0034">An entity presents its <xref base="SL131365" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0018">cash flows<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0030"/></ph></xref> from<xref base="SL131366" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0021"> operating<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0268"/></ph></xref>, <xref base="SL131367" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0024">investing<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0202"/></ph></xref> and <xref base="SL131368" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0027">financing activities<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0130"/></ph></xref> in a manner which is most appropriate to its business. Classification by activity provides information that allows users                     to assess the impact of those activities on the financial position              of the entity and the amount of its <xref base="SL131363" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0014">cash<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0028"/></ph></xref> and <xref base="SL131364" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0015">cash equivalents<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0029"/></ph></xref>. This information may also be used to evaluate the relationships among those activities.</p></body></paragraph>